FR941025-2-00045 FR941025-2-00035 Capozzi Bros. Fuel Co. Bridgeport, CT, Lee&hyph;0143, Reporting Requirements Capozzi Bros. Fuel Co. filed an Application for Exception from the Energy Information Administration (EIA) requirement that it file Form EIA&hyph;782B, the ``Resellers'/Retailers' Monthly Petroleum Product Sales Report.'' In considering this request, the DOE found that the firm was not suffering a gross inequity, a serious hardship or an unfair distribution of burdens. Accordingly, on August 16, 1994, the DOE issued a Proposed Decision and Order determining that the exception request should be denied. Cooperative Oil Company, Osage, IA, Lee&hyph;0132, Reporting Requirements Cooperative Oil Company filed an Application for Exception from the requirement that it file Form EIA&hyph;782B, the ``Resellers'/ Retailers' Monthly Petroleum Product Sales Report.'' In considering the request, the DOE found that the firm was not experiencing a serious hardship or adversely affected by the reporting requirement in a way that was significantly different from the burden borne by similar reporting firms. Accordingly, on August 19, 1994, the DOE issued a Proposed Decision and Order determining that the exception request should be denied. Hattenhauer Dist. Co. The Dalles, OR, Lee&hyph;0146, Reporting Requirements Hattenhauer Distributing Company filed an Application for Exception from the Energy Information Administration (EIA) requirement that it file Form EIA&hyph;782B, the ``Resellers'/Retailers' Monthly Petroleum Product Sales Report.'' In considering this request, the DOE found that the firm was not suffering a gross inequity or serious hardship. Accordingly, on August 19, 1994, the DOE issued a Proposed Decision and Order determining that the exception request should be denied. Johnson Oil Company Gaston, IN, Lee&hyph;0121, Reporting Requirements Johnson Oil Company filed an Application for Exception from the Energy Information Administration (EIA) requirement that it file Form EIA&hyph;782B, the ``Resellers'/Retailers' Monthly Petroleum Product Sales Report.'' In considering this request, the DOE found that the firm was not suffering a gross inequity or serious hardship. Accordingly, on August 19, 1994 the DOE issued a Proposed Decision and Order determining that the exception request should be denied. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;26364 Filed 10&hyph;24&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 6450&hyph;01&hyph;P
